						<summary>

						<p>On a stone in front of the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>No date. Written in the Telugu-Kannada characters of 8th-9th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>Badly damaged. Only a part of the <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> commencing with <hi rend="italic">Ari-durdhara-vara</hi> etc., is preserved. As it refers to solar family, it might belong to the Rēnāṭi-Choḷa period.</p>						

						</summary>
